We have a chain in place to sell our house and move to buy another
property. This new property is going through probate. However, the
property we want to buy is in hot demand and is being chased by a
number of potential buyers.

Even though we have a chain in place that is ready to move, the agents
acting on behalf of the sellers want us to exchange contracts on our
current property before we exchange on the new property. We don't like
this - because we could end up without a roof over our head.
Therefore, we have suggested putting a bridging loan in place - in the
unlikely event that our current chain falls through.

To accept this, the agent wants to see a letter from a bank by the end
of this week confirming that an &quot;open-ended&quot; bridging loan is in
place. Any ideas on bridging loans? Who to go with? What's the cost?
How long to get them in place? The amount is £570K. Our current
mortgage lender is Abbey.

Thanks
</POST>
