My guess (based on experience 20 years ago) is that you will find it
hard to get an open ended bridging loan which you could not support
from your income indefinietly. If you could support it (as well as any
existign mortgage), then you might as well simply get a mortgage on
the property you are buying and accept that will own two at the same
time for a while.

As others have poitned out, it's not clear from the posting where the
bottleneck is.  If they are still waiting for probate for the house yo
uwish to buy then a loan won't help.

Probate can take ages and it's often hard to predict when it will be
granted.  Have the executors paid the inheritance tax yet?

